In order to set this up from scratch, flash the SD card and load NOOBS:
https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/noobs/
Use SDFormatter
https://www.raspberrypi.org/learning/software-guide/quickstart/
https://www.raspberrypi.org/help/noobs-setup/2/
Follow this in order to get the basic OS installed.

Log in with pi and raspberry

SETUP WIFI:
https://learn.adafruit.com/adafruits-raspberry-pi-lesson-3-network-setup/setting-up-wifi-with-occidentalis
sudo nano /etc/network/interfaces
auto lo

iface lo inet loopback
iface eth0 inet dhcp

allow-hotplug wlan0
auto wlan0


iface wlan0 inet dhcp
        wpa-ssid "ssid"
        wpa-psk "password"



REBOOT now u have wifi yay



Next we need to update the repos:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install git
go to ~/ and run
git clone https://github.com/KAPastor/TheBox.git
cd to SystemSetup
 chmod 755 InitialSystemSetup
run ./InitialSystemSetup.sh
